(2313, 7, 171, 'description', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Ulcinj, a town&nbsp;on th</span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><img style="float: left;" title="ulcinj" src="../upload-media/slike/ulcinj_1.jpg" alt="ulcinj" width="213" height="160" /></span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">e border&nbsp;with Albania,&nbsp;the&nbsp;famous&nbsp;and as a former&nbsp;capital of&nbsp;the Adriatic pirates, and also invaders who&nbsp;laid cla</span></span><span style="font-size: small;"></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">im&nbsp;to it for&nbsp;many centuries. However, today the more notable as the city&nbsp;with the largest increase in&nbsp;tourism&nbsp;in </span></span><span style="font-size: small;"></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Montenegro.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Its&nbsp;Mediterranean climate&nbsp;has given it&nbsp;a long, hot&nbsp;and&nbsp;dry summers&nbsp; versus&nbsp;rainy&nbsp;and windy winters. Here,&nbsp;temperatures&nbsp;rarely&nbsp;exceed 35&nbsp;degrees&nbsp;in summer&nbsp;and rarely&nbsp;fall&nbsp;below zero&nbsp;in winter.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Ulcinj is connecte</span></span><span style="font-size: small;"></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">d to other coastal towns with Adriatic road, and&nbsp;both the airport&nbsp;(Tivat&nbsp;and Podgorica)&nbsp;are&nbsp;about 70&nbsp;kilometers away. In addition to&nbsp;the many beaches,&nbsp;old town&nbsp;with&nbsp;many cultural and historical monuments&nbsp;and Ada&nbsp;Bojana,&nbsp;Ulcinj&nbsp;is situated near&nbsp;the&nbsp;two lakes, Sasko and Skadar. Velika&nbsp;plaza,&nbsp;which is&nbsp;located&nbsp;near the city,&nbsp;with&nbsp;its 13&nbsp;kilometers is the longest beach on the&nbsp;Adriatic.&nbsp;His&nbsp;fine&nbsp;and healing&nbsp;sand each year&nbsp;attracts more&nbsp;tourists. The most famous town plaza is named Mala plaza. Is surrounded by an attractive boulevard, Corso, that its full glory experienced in the warm summer nights. For water,&nbsp;at the women''s&nbsp;beach, it is believed&nbsp;to cure&nbsp;infertility&nbsp;with its mixture of&nbsp;sulfur,&nbsp;radium&nbsp;and sea&nbsp;salt.&nbsp;The whole&nbsp;area of&nbsp;&#8203;&#8203;Ulcinj is rich in&nbsp;small&nbsp;and hidden beaches&nbsp;that offer&nbsp;privacy and&nbsp;an escape from the crowds.</span></span></p>\r\n<form style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The fish you&nbsp;catch&nbsp;you can&nbsp;make yourself&nbsp;or visit&nbsp;one of the many&nbsp;restaurants where&nbsp;are the seafood&nbsp;specialties.&nbsp;Ada&nbsp;is&nbsp;also&nbsp;one of the&nbsp;three&nbsp;IBA&nbsp;(Important Bird Areas)&nbsp;in Montenegro. Over 200 species of birds&nbsp;is due to&nbsp;mating,&nbsp;nesting, or&nbsp;rest&nbsp;on their way totropical regions. At Ada Bojana&nbsp;is worth&nbsp;to come&nbsp;for peace and unique&nbsp;atmosphere&nbsp;where you can enjoy the beautiful sunsets.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">One&nbsp;of the hallmarks&nbsp;of Ulcinj&nbsp;are olives, and their&nbsp;greatest number can be found&nbsp;in the bay Valdanos. Unlike&nbsp;the Long Beach&nbsp;here prevails&nbsp;gravel&nbsp;and&nbsp;water is&nbsp;more transparent&nbsp;and more suitable for&nbsp;scuba diving and&nbsp;deep sea&nbsp;exploration.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">At first&nbsp;glance, the&nbsp;old town of&nbsp;Ulcinj&nbsp;seems to&nbsp;rise from the&nbsp;sea. One of&nbsp;the oldest on the Adriatic coast, was founded&nbsp;during&nbsp;the Greek&nbsp;colonization&nbsp;of this&nbsp;part of the coast.&nbsp;The turbulent history of&nbsp;his&nbsp;legacy&nbsp;has left many&nbsp;in the&nbsp;beauty.&nbsp;Here you&nbsp;can&nbsp;find the remains of&nbsp;oriental architecture, only one in&nbsp;Montenegro. Walking&nbsp;the ancient&nbsp;streets&nbsp;and visit the bazaar&nbsp;will bring you back&nbsp;at another time.&nbsp;The most significant&nbsp;is the&nbsp;Sinan&nbsp;Pasha&nbsp;Mosque from the 18<sup>th</sup> century. &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><img style="margin: 2px; float: right; border: 1px solid black;" title="Ulcinj " src="../upload-media/slike/ulcinj2.jpg" alt="Ulcinj " width="249" height="182" /></span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"> </span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">D</span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">efinitely&nbsp;worth&nbsp;visiting&nbsp;the Church of&nbsp;St. Nicholas&nbsp;accompanied by&nbsp;an interesting history. Specifically, the original&nbsp;monastery&nbsp;by the Turks&nbsp;turned&nbsp;mosque,&nbsp;but was laterre-processed into the church.&nbsp;Will&nbsp;elicit&nbsp;sighs&nbsp;and gorgeous buildings&nbsp;Castle&nbsp;Balsica&nbsp;and the Venice&nbsp;Palace. &nbsp;The walls&nbsp;of the city are particularly interesting&nbsp;because of its&nbsp;age&nbsp;and form.&nbsp;As a break from&nbsp;the tour&nbsp;of historic&nbsp;value, you can relax&nbsp;in one&nbsp;of the many&nbsp;cafes&nbsp;and restaurants or custom&nbsp;one of&nbsp;a gallery or archaeological museums.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Grad Ulcinj is a town of versatility. Whether you are looking for peace and privacy, an unforgettable night out, or an active vacation, this is a city for you. You can even try the three types of fishing: sea, river (the river Bojana) and lake (the Sasko and Skadar lake). Diving and explore shipwrecks and ruins of the city, cycling through the olive groves or stroll on the beach are only a small part of the magic of Ulcinj, the town simply calls for new coming.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n</form>', 'Ulcinj, grad na granici s Albanijom thulcinje, poznati i kao biv?i kapitala Jadranskog gusara, a tako&#273;er i osvaja&#269;a koji su propisani zahtjev za nju za mnoga stolje&#263;a. Me&#273;utim, danas vi?e isti&#269;e kao grad s najve&#263;im porastom turizma u Crnoj Gori.\r\n\r\nNjegova mediteranska klima je dao to dugo, toplo i suho ljeto u odnosu na ki?ovito i vjetrovito zime. Evo, temperature rijetko prelaze 35 stupnjeva u ljeto i rijetko padaju ispod nule zimi.\r\n\r\nUlcinj je povezan s drugim primorskim gradovima s Jadranske magistrale, a oba zra&#269;na luka (Tivat i Podgorica) oko 70 km daleko. Osim brojnih pla?a, stari grad s brojnim kulturno-povijesnim spomenicima i Ada Bojana, Ulcinj nalazi se u blizini dva jezera, Saska i Skadarsko. Velika plaza, koja se nalazi u neposrednoj blizini grada, sa svojim 13 km je najdu?i pla?a na Jadranu. Njegov fini i ljekovito pijesak svake godine privla&#269;i sve vi?e turista. Najpoznatiji grad plaza se zove Mala plaza. Je okru?en atraktivnim bulevar, Corso, da svom punom sjaju do?ivio u toplim ljetnim no&#263;ima. Za vode na ?enske pla?i, on je vjerovao da lije&#269;e neplodnost s mje?avinom sumpora, radija i morske soli. Cijelo podru&#269;je Ulcinja je bogata u malim i skrivenih pla?a koje nude privatnost i bijeg od gu?ve.\r\n\r\nRibe ?to vas uhvatiti mo?ete napraviti sami ili posjetite jedan od brojnih restorana u kojem su se morski specijaliteti. Ada je tako&#273;er jedan od tri IBA (Va?ni Bird Areas) u Crnoj Gori. Preko 200 vrsta ptica je zbog parenja, gnije?&#273;enja, odnosno ostatak na putu totropical regijama. Na Adi Bojani je vrijedno da se za mir i jedinstvenu atmosferu, gdje mo?ete u?ivati &#8203;&#8203;u prekrasnom zalasku sunca.\r\n\r\nJedan od simbola Ulcinju su masline, a njihov najve&#263;i broj se mo?e na&#263;i u uvali Valdanos. Za razliku od Long Beach ovdje prevladava ?ljunak i voda je transparentniji i vi?e pogodna za ronjenje i duboko more istra?ivanje.\r\n\r\nNa prvi pogled, Stari grad Ulcinj &#269;ini porasti od mora. Jedan od najstarijih na Jadranu, osnovan je u vrijeme gr&#269;ke kolonizacije ovog dijela obale. Burna povijest njegove ostav?tine je ostavio mnoge u ljepoti. Ovdje mo?ete prona&#263;i ostatke orijentalne arhitekture, samo jedan u Crnoj Gori. Pje?a&#269;ka drevne ulice i posjetite bazar &#263;e vas vratiti u neko drugo vrijeme. Najzna&#269;ajniji je d?amija Sinan-pa?a iz 18. stolje&#263;a.\r\n\r\nUlcinj\r\n\r\nDefinitivno vrijedi posjetiti crkvu Sv popra&#263;en zanimljive povijesti. Naime, originalni samostan Turci okrenuo d?amija, ali je laterre obra&#273;en u crkvu. Ho&#263;e izmamiti uzdahe i prekrasna zgrada Dvorac Balsica i Venecija pala&#269;a. Zidovi grada su posebno zanimljiva zbog svoje starosti i oblika. Kao pauzu od turneje povijesne vrijednosti, mo?ete se opustiti u jednom od brojnih kafi&#263;a i restorana ili obi&#269;aj jedan od galerije ili arheolo?kim muzejima.\r\n\r\nGrad Ulcinj je grad svestranosti. Bilo da ste u potrazi za mir i privatnost, nezaboravan no&#263;ni out, ili aktivni odmor, ovo je grad za vas. Mo?ete &#269;ak probati tri vrste ribolova: more, rijeke (rijeka Bojana) i jezero (Sasko i Skadarsko jezero). Ronjenje i istra?ivati &#8203;&#8203;olupina i ru?evine grada, biciklizam kroz maslinike ili ?etati na pla?i, samo su mali dio magije Ulcinja, grad naprosto poziva na novi dolaze.', 'content_type'),
