h of Zeta and Moraca, are the remains of the old town Duklje, which are one of the most important historical monuments of Montenegro. <br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">In Podgorica is also a Montenegrin National Theatre, under whose auspices of the functioning and Children''s National Theatre. Museum of the City of Podgorica is home to a variety of items from the Illyrian and Roman times, and is divided into four categories: archaeological, ethnographic, historical and cultural-historical. The most important memorial museum in Montenegro, Mark Miljan Museum, also located in the capital</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Since the museum is still important to mention The natural. A place not to be missed is and Castle of Petrovic, the former seat of King Nikola, now converted into an art gallery. Itself The palace is surrounded by a beautiful park where you can and also find and Perjanicki home chapel. Symbol Podgorica and two churches - one new, one old. Temple of Christ''s resurrection is the largest and most beautiful church in Montenegro, while at the foothills of Gorica is the St. George Church, built in the 14th Ages. <br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">City of opposites that complement each other, Podgorica offers something for everyone. Large shopping centers, bike trails, exciting nightlife - Podgorica everyone welcomes</span></span></p>', '&#1057;&#1090;&#1086;&#1083;&#1080;&#1094;&#1072; &#1063;&#1077;&#1088;&#1085;&#1086;&#1075;&#1086;&#1088;&#1080;&#1080; &#1085;&#1072;&#1093;&#1086;&#1076;&#1080;&#1090;&#1089;&#1103; &#1074; Bjelopavlickoj &#1087;&#1088;&#1086;&#1089;&#1090;&#1086; &#1080; &#1083;&#1077;&#1078