(2767, 5, 174, 'description', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">In the vicinity of Niksic, in Bjelopavlickoj plain, is the monastery Ostrog. This fascinating example of the architecture lies along the nearly vertical edge Ostro&scaron;ka beams. Founded in the 17th century by St. Basil of Ostrog, who was buried here. There are reports of thousands of miraculous healings that are believed to have attained the power of the Holy Vassily.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The monastery is divided into upper and lower complex. The lower complex are the monastery and church of the Holy Trinity, built in the 1820th year. The upper monastery gives the impression as if cut out of the mountains. Both monasteries can be commended numerous frescos. Between them in 2005. built the church of the Holy Martyrs Stojan, and there are a number of cave churches, which represent a great historical value. Ostrog is one of the most visited pilgrimage site in the Balkans. It is visited by Orthodox and Catholics, and Muslims from around the world.</span></span></p>', 'В непо', 'content_type'),
(2768, 7, 174, 'description', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">In the vicinity of Niksic, in Bjelopavlickoj plain, is the monastery Ostrog. This fascinating example of the architecture lies along the nearly vertical edge Ostro&scaron;ka beams. Founded in the 17th century by St. Basil of Ostrog, who was buried here. There are reports of thousands of miraculous healings that are believed to have attained the power of the Holy Vassily.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The monastery is divided into upper and lower complex. The lower complex are the monastery and church of the Holy Trinity, built in the 1820th year. The upper monastery gives the impression as if cut out of the mountains. Both monasteries can be commended numerous frescos. Between them in 2005. built the church of the Holy Martyrs Stojan, and there are a number of cave churches, which represent a great historical value. Ostrog is one of the most visited pilgrimage site in the Balkans. It is visited by Orthodox and Catholics, and Muslims from around the world.</span></span></p>', 'U blizini Nikšića, u Bjelopavlickoj ravnici, je samostan Ostrog. Ova fascinantna primjer arhitekture leži uz gotovo okomitim rub Ostroška greda. Osnovan je u 17. stoljeću sv Bazilija Ostroga, koji je tu i pokopan. Postoje izvješća tisuća ', 'content_type'),
