(3004, 5, 304, 'short_description', '<p style="color: #003580; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16.666667938232422px;">Set within the peaceful Komnenovo Ethno Village located on the banks of Lake Plav, Hotel Kula Damjanova offers private lake access, a beach and a refined rustic restaurant serving traditional Montenegrin cuisine.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #003580; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16.666667938232422px;">Kula&rsquo;s rooms are carefully decorated in local ethno style with hand-crafted carpets and textiles. They offer wooden floors, stony walls and a flat-screen TV with cable reception.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #003580; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16.666667938232422px;">The public areas are furnished in a similar authentic local style and feature hand-carved wooden furniture and a bar with a fireplace. Free Wi-Fi is available in Kula&rsquo;s public areas.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #003580; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16.666667938232422px;">Numerous hiking and biking paths are available around the hotel. There is also a football pitch. Lake Plav offers excellent possibilities for fishing.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #003580; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16.666667938232422px;">Guests can reach the centre of Plav within a 1.2 km walk. Grlja Waterfall is 18 km away. Podgorica with its airport is 140 km away. Free on-site parking is provided.</p>', '<p style="color: #003580; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16.666667938232422px;">Отель Kula Damjanova находит', 'property_type'),
