(170, 'Privacy statement (En)', 342, 0, NULL, 2, '', '', '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Privacy statement</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong> </strong><strong>Privacy policy</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">We highly value your trust in choosing Sunnymontenegro.com for your online hotel reservation. Therefore, we will duly and diligently safeguard and protect the privacy and confidentiality of your personal details (including your credit card details).</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">This privacy policy applies to all of our services (whether accessed or made available online or through any other platform or device (hereafter collectively referred to as the "website")).</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong> </strong><strong>Information collection</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">When you make a reservation for a hotel (or any other type of accommodation), you will be asked to complete online forms providing for: your name, (home or office) address, (business or private) email address, (mobile, home or office) telephone number, credit card details (i.e. credit card type and number, CVC code, expiration date, credit card holder name) and to the extent available, reservation preferences and smoking preference. This information is required to process, book and complete your reservation (including the sending of a confirmation email of the booking to you).</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong> </strong><strong>Disclosure of personal details</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">For our services, we shall collect for the following purposes the following information:</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><em>Reservation orders:</em> For the purposes of completing your booking and save for disclosures required by law, criminal investigations, subpoenas or court orders, we will only disclose your name, contact details and the credit card details to the relevant hotel with which a booking is made. However, please note that from time to time, we may use third party distributors which provide certain services and functions for and on our behalf. These third party distributors may have access to (part of your) personal information in order to perform their services and functions, but are subject to a confidentiality obligation pursuant to which they cannot use, share or disclose the information for any other purpose.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><em>Surveys:</em> By completing a booking, you agree to receive an invitation email to complete our guest review form which we will promptly send to you after your stay at the hotel. The review can also be completed anonymously. By completing the guest review, you agree that the completed guest review can be uploaded to and used on our website at the relevant hotel information page and on such other platforms and social media (wholly or partly) owned, controlled, managed or hosted by us or our trusted business partners for the sole purpose of informing (future) customers on the service (level) and quality of the relevant hotel. We reserve the right to adjust, refuse or remove review forms at our sole discretion. The guest review form should be regarded as a survey and does not include any (further commercial) offers, invitations or incentives whatsoever.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><em>Newsletters and other information:</em> If you wish to subscribe for our newsletter or wish to receive promotional communications or other information from us (in respect to our affiliated companies'' or business partners'' products or services), we offer you the option to "Opt in" for this service. If you no longer wish to receive our newsletter and other promotional communications, you can simply click on the unsubscribe link.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><em>Visitor''s registration, log in and use of "cookies" and web beacons:</em> For (improvement of) our service and product, we use (temporary and persistent) cookies, authorised third parties cookies, web beacons and/or other technologies to collect non-personally identifiable data such as IP address, browser type and Internet Service Provider (ISP) and (for users of our service through a mobile device) Unique Device Identifier, Operating System and Latitude/Longitude (the "Non-PII"). This non-personally identifiable data helps us to track browsing behaviour, to create specific or tailor-made offers or advertisements, and to monitor and record the visits and use of our website(s).</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">In order to understand how people use our website and for marketing analysis and quality improvement purposes, we collect, record, process and use on an anonymous basis various data and information, such as the total amount of transactions, viewed web pages, referring/exit pages, platform type, date/time stamp information and details like the number and location of (mouse) clicks on a given page, mouse movements, scrolling activity and the (search) words you use and the text you type while being on and using our website (the "Data").</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Furthermore, we will use your Non-PII for behavioural targeting. We will also maintain a record of your Non-PII for the purposes of potential legal investigations involving fraud, misuse and criminal investigation.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Please note that from time to time, we may use third party service providers for marketing analysis and quality improvement purposes (the "Service Providers"). We may also use Service Providers to track detailed visitor activity on specific pages. These Service Providers collect, use, monitor and report on the Data and other information and statistics, and they analyze online activities on our website. The information about your use of our website (including the Data, your Non-PII) may be transmitted to and stored on the servers of the Service Providers. Furthermore, the Service Providers may also transfer the collected information to third parties where required to do so by law, or where such third parties process the information on the Service Provider''s behalf.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">When visiting and using our website, we do not share any personal information about our customers with our Service Providers and the Service Providers will not collect any personally identifiable information ("PII"). PII does not include your IP address, browser type, Internet Service Provider , Unique Device Identifier, Operating System and Latitude/Longitude. We may share and disclose your personal details and information to a governmental or investigative authority if required by law (or any regulation having the force of law), legal process, criminal investigation, court order or subpoena.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><em>About cookies and web beacons:</em> Cookies are text files stored at your computer, either temporary or persistent on your hard drive. Cookies are used for authenticating, session tracking (state maintenance) and maintaining specific information about the use and users of our website, such as site preferences or the contents of their electronic shopping carts. Cookie files may also be placed at your computer by our trusted third-party advertising companies for the purposes as set out in this paragraph. The data collected by these cookies are completely anonymous. If you prefer, you can delete all cookies that are already on your computer''s hard drive by searching for files with "cookie" in it and delete it and for the future, you can edit your browser options such that (future) cookies are blocked; however, please note that if you do this you may not be able to use the full functionality of our website. For more information about (the use and decline of) cookies, please visit: <a href="http://www.allaboutcookies.org/" target="_blank">www.allaboutcookies.org</a></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Web beacon consists of a small string of software code that represents a graphic image request on a Web page or email. There may or may not be a visible graphic image associated with the web beacon and often the image is designed to blend into the background of a Web page or email. Web beacons can be used for many purposes - including site traffic reporting, unique visitor counts, advertising auditing and reporting, and personalization. Web beacons used by Sunnymontenegro.com collect only anonymous data.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong> </strong><strong>Protect and safeguard your online privacy</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Please note that, in accordance with European personal data protection laws, strict security procedures are observed within Sunnymontenegro.com to prevent personal data misuse and unauthorised access.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Sunnymontenegro.com uses trusted and recognised advertising online marketing and analytics companies committed to building consumer awareness and establishing responsible business and data management practices and standards. Most of these companies are a member of the Network Advertising Initiative ("NAI"). The NAI members participate fully in the NAI Principles and offer a general opt-out function of the behavioural advertising. Please visit <a href="http://www.networkadvertising.org/managing/opt_out.asp">www.networkadvertising.org</a> to identify the NAI members that have placed an advertising cookie file on your computer. To opt out of an NAI member''s behavioural advertising programme, simply check the box that corresponds to the company from which you wish to opt out.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Please note that opting out of a network does not mean you will no longer receive or be subject to online advertising or marketing analysis. It does mean that the network from which you opted out will no longer deliver ads tailored to your web preferences and usage patterns.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong> </strong><strong>Protect and secure your credit card information</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">In order to protect and safeguard the personal data provided to us, we have implemented and use appropriate business systems and procedures. For example, your credit card information is transmitted to us through a secure server protocol, which encrypts all your personal and credit card details. The encryption method used is the industry standard "Secure Socket Layer" (SSL) technology. Our SSL certificate has been issued by Thawte: <a href="http://www.thawte.com/" target="_blank">www.thawte.com</a> <br /> Furthermore, we have implemented and use security procedures and technical and physical restrictions for accessing and using personal information. Only authorised employees are permitted to access personal information for performing their duties in respect to our services.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Our server and network are protected by firewalls against unauthorised access and we have intrusion detection systems that monitor and detect unauthorised (attempts to) access or misuse our servers.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Your credit card details will be kept by us up to maximum 10 days after a booking is made. After that period, your credit card data will be deleted.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong> </strong><strong>Control over your data</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">You always have the right to review the personal data you have stored with us. You can request your personal data by emailing us at: <a href="mailto:%20customer.service@booking.com?subject=Request%20personal%20data">customer.service@Sunnymontenegro.com</a> <br /> Please state ''request personal data'' in the subject line of your email.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">If your personal data is incorrect, we will change it upon your request. You can also ask Sunnymontenegro.com to remove your personal data from its database by sending us an email to the aforementioned email address.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong> </strong><strong>When does Sunnymontenegro.com send you emails?</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">After you have made a booking, you will receive a confirmation message with all the information about your booking. You may take this confirmation to the hotel as proof of the reservation. Shortly prior to your arrival date we may send you an email which may include information on your destination and may provide certain information and offers (including third party offers to the extent that you have actively opted in for this information) relevant to your booking and destination. Furthermore, after your stay at the hotel, we will send you the guest review survey, which we appreciate to be filled in by you. Your completed guest review form may be uploaded onto and used on the relevant hotel''s information page on our website and on such other platforms and social media (wholly or partly) owned, controlled, managed or hosted by us or our trusted business partners for the sole purpose of informing (future) customers of your opinion of the service (level) and quality of the hotel. To the extent that you have "Opted in" you may receive our newsletter or other information from time to time.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong> </strong><strong>Contact</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Sunnymontenegro.com B.V. is the responsible party for the processing of the personal data. Sunnymontenegro.com B.V. is a private limited liability company, incorporated under the laws of the Netherlands and has its offices at Weteringschans 28, 1017 SG, Amsterdam, the Netherlands. The Dutch Data Protection Authority Notification number is 1288246.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">If you have any suggestions or remarks about this privacy statement, please send an email to: <a href="mailto:%20customer.service@booking.com?subject=Privacy%20statement">customer.service@Sunnymontenegro.com</a></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">We are at all times entitled to change the way we collect, transmit and process the personal information and such other information as we may deem necessary. This Privacy Statement may therefore be amended from time to time in order to reflect the latest changes.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>', '23.8569', '19.519132', 'privacy-statement-en'),
(171, 'Ulcinj (En)', 285, 0, NULL, 2, 'Ulcinj', 'Ulcinj', 'Ulcinj Montenegro', 'Ulcinj Montenegro accommodation', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Ulcinj, a town&nbsp;on th</span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><img style="float: left;" title="ulcinj" src="../upload-media/slike/ulcinj_1.jpg" alt="ulcinj" width="213" height="160" /></span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">e border&nbsp;with Albania,&nbsp;the&nbsp;famous&nbsp;and as a former&nbsp;capital of&nbsp;the Adriatic pirates, and also invaders who&nbsp;laid cla</span></span><span style="font-size: small;"></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">im&nbsp;to it for&nbsp;many centuries. However, today the more notable as the city&nbsp;with the largest increase in&nbsp;tourism&nbsp;in </span></span><span style="font-size: small;"></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Montenegro.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Its&nbsp;Mediterranean climate&nbsp;has given it&nbsp;a long, hot&nbsp;and&nbsp;dry summers&nbsp; versus&nbsp;rainy&nbsp;and windy winters. Here,&nbsp;temperatures&nbsp;rarely&nbsp;exceed 35&nbsp;degrees&nbsp;in summer&nbsp;and rarely&nbsp;fall&nbsp;below zero&nbsp;in winter.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Ulcinj is connecte</span></span><span style="font-size: small;"></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">d to other coastal towns with Adriatic road, and&nbsp;both the airport&nbsp;(Tivat&nbsp;and Podgorica)&nbsp;are&nbsp;about 70&nbsp;kilometers away. In addition to&nbsp;the many beaches,&nbsp;old town&nbsp;with&nbsp;many cultural and historical monuments&nbsp;and Ada&nbsp;Bojana,&nbsp;Ulcinj&nbsp;is situated near&nbsp;the&nbsp;two lakes, Sasko and Skadar. Velika&nbsp;plaza,&nbsp;which is&nbsp;located&nbsp;near the city,&nbsp;with&nbsp;its 13&nbsp;kilometers is the longest beach on the&nbsp;Adriatic.&nbsp;His&nbsp;fine&nbsp;and healing&nbsp;sand each year&nbsp;attracts more&nbsp;tourists. The most famous town plaza is named Mala plaza. Is surrounded by an attractive boulevard, Corso, that its full glory experienced in the warm summer nights. For water,&nbsp;at the women''s&nbsp;beach, it is believed&nbsp;to cure&nbsp;infertility&nbsp;with its mixture of&nbsp;sulfur,&nbsp;radium&nbsp;and sea&nbsp;salt.&nbsp;The whole&nbsp;area of&nbsp;&#8203;&#8203;Ulcinj is rich in&nbsp;small&nbsp;and hidden beaches&nbsp;that offer&nbsp;privacy and&nbsp;an escape from the crowds.</span></span></p>\r\n<form style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The fish you&nbsp;catch&nbsp;you can&nbsp;make yourself&nbsp;or visit&nbsp;one of the many&nbsp;restaurants where&nbsp;are the seafood&nbsp;specialties.&nbsp;Ada&nbsp;is&nbsp;also&nbsp;one of the&nbsp;three&nbsp;IBA&nbsp;(Important Bird Areas)&nbsp;in Montenegro. Over 200 species of birds&nbsp;is due to&nbsp;mating,&nbsp;nesting, or&nbsp;rest&nbsp;on their way totropical regions. At Ada Bojana&nbsp;is worth&nbsp;to come&nbsp;for peace and unique&nbsp;atmosphere&nbsp;where you can enjoy the beautiful sunsets.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">One&nbsp;of the hallmarks&nbsp;of Ulcinj&nbsp;are olives, and their&nbsp;greatest number can be found&nbsp;in the bay Valdanos. Unlike&nbsp;the Long Beach&nbsp;here prevails&nbsp;gravel&nbsp;and&nbsp;water is&nbsp;more transparent&nbsp;and more suitable for&nbsp;scuba diving and&nbsp;deep sea&nbsp;exploration.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">At first&nbsp;glance, the&nbsp;old town of&nbsp;Ulcinj&nbsp;seems to&nbsp;rise from the&nbsp;sea. One of&nbsp;the oldest on the Adriatic coast, was founded&nbsp;during&nbsp;the Greek&nbsp;colonization&nbsp;of this&nbsp;part of the coast.&nbsp;The turbulent history of&nbsp;his&nbsp;legacy&nbsp;has left many&nbsp;in the&nbsp;beauty.&nbsp;Here you&nbsp;can&nbsp;find the remains of&nbsp;oriental architecture, only one in&nbsp;Montenegro. Walking&nbsp;the ancient&nbsp;streets&nbsp;and visit the bazaar&nbsp;will bring you back&nbsp;at another time.&nbsp;The most significant&nbsp;is the&nbsp;Sinan&nbsp;Pasha&nbsp;Mosque from the 18<sup>th</sup> century. &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><img style="margin: 2px; float: right; border: 1px solid black;" title="Ulcinj " src="../upload-media/slike/ulcinj2.jpg" alt="Ulcinj " width="249" height="182" /></span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"> </span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">D</span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">efinitely&nbsp;worth&nbsp;visiting&nbsp;the Church of&nbsp;St. Nicholas&nbsp;accompanied by&nbsp;an interesting history. Specifically, the original&nbsp;monastery&nbsp;by the Turks&nbsp;turned&nbsp;mosque,&nbsp;but was laterre-processed into the church.&nbsp;Will&nbsp;elicit&nbsp;sighs&nbsp;and gorgeous buildings&nbsp;Castle&nbsp;Balsica&nbsp;and the Venice&nbsp;Palace. &nbsp;The walls&nbsp;of the city are particularly interesting&nbsp;because of its&nbsp;age&nbsp;and form.&nbsp;As a break from&nbsp;the tour&nbsp;of historic&nbsp;value, you can relax&nbsp;in one&nbsp;of the many&nbsp;cafes&nbsp;and restaurants or custom&nbsp;one of&nbsp;a gallery or archaeological museums.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Grad Ulcinj is a town of versatility. Whether you are looking for peace and privacy, an unforgettable night out, or an active vacation, this is a city for you. You can even try the three types of fishing: sea, river (the river Bojana) and lake (the Sasko and Skadar lake). Diving and explore shipwrecks and ruins of the city, cycling through the olive groves or stroll on the beach are only a small part of the magic of Ulcinj, the town simply calls for new coming.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n</form>', '41.929722', '19.224291', 'ulcinj-en'),
(172, 'Podgorica (En)', 291, 0, NULL, 2, 'Podgorica', 'Podgorica, accommodation, tourism', 'Podgorica capital town montenegro', 'Podgorica tourism montenegro', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><img style="float: left; margin: 2px; border: 1px solid black;" title="Podgorica" src="../upload-media/podgorica_4.jpg" alt="Podgorica" width="300" height="225" />The Capital of Montenegro&nbsp;is located in&nbsp;Bjelopavlickoj&nbsp;plain&nbsp;and it lies on&nbsp;six rivers.&nbsp;Near the airport,&nbsp;and the fact that&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;midwaybetween&nbsp;the sea&nbsp;and snow-covered&nbsp;mountains&nbsp;have made&nbsp;themost important&nbsp;crossroads&nbsp;of&nbsp;Podgorica.&nbsp;City&nbsp;of turbulent&nbsp;history,known for its&nbsp;mixture&nbsp;of architectural&nbsp;styles.&nbsp;From the&nbsp;narrow&nbsp;streetand stone houses&nbsp;in&nbsp;Drac and&nbsp;in Stara&nbsp;Varos,&nbsp;to large,&nbsp;glasscovered&nbsp;buildings,&nbsp;features&nbsp;Pogorice&nbsp;a large number&nbsp;of bridges.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Despite the rapid urbanization of the city, green space in Podgorica and still has in abundance. The two largest parks, Njegos I Karadjordjevo ideal place to escape from the heat and rest. For those who want to escape the city crowd, they must walk in the surrounding hills, Gorica and Ljubovic. History lovers can visit the Monument to the Unknown Hero in Gorica, a symbol of Podgorica. If you want to feel the spirit of old Podgorica, you can always visit the Old Varos, which also contains two mosques built by the original six. You can continue to walk the famous stairs and visit the remains Nemanjinog city, the oldest part o</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">f Podgorica. Another highlight is a Sun Tower, built in the 18th Ages. Near the town at the mouth of Zeta and Moraca, are the remains of the old town Duklje, which are one of the most important historical monuments of Montenegro. <br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">In Podgorica is also a Montenegrin National Theatre, under whose auspices of the functioning and Children''s National Theatre. Museum of the City of Podgorica is home to a variety of items from the Illyrian and Roman times, and is divided into four categories: archaeological, ethnographic, historical and cultural-historical. The most important memorial museum in Montenegro, Mark Miljan Museum, also located in the capital</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Since the museum is still important to mention The natural. A place not to be missed is and Castle of Petrovic, the former seat of King Nikola, now converted into an art gallery. Itself The palace is surrounded by a beautiful park where you can and also find and Perjanicki home chapel. Symbol Podgorica and two churches - one new, one old. Temple of Christ''s resurrection is the largest and most beautiful church in Montenegro, while at the foothills of Gorica is the St. George Church, built in the 14th Ages. <br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">City of opposites that complement each other, Podgorica offers something for everyone. Large shopping centers, bike trails, exciting nightlife - Podgorica everyone welcomes</span></span></p>', '42.439200', '19.266000', 'podgorica-en'),
(173, 'Zabljak', 295, 0, NULL, 2, 'Zabljak', 'Zabljak, Montenegro skiing snowboarding', 'Zabljak, Montenegro skiing snowboarding', 'Zabljak je na sjevernom dijelu crne gore', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Zabljak</strong></span><br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">With its 1450 meters Zabljak is the highest village in the Balkans. The main destination for those wishing winter sports, is located on Mount Durmitor, which is also a national park. Its unspoiled nature, as well as benefits for both the winter, and summer tourism attracts more visitors from Europe and the world.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Air on Zabljak is sub-mountainous and alpine, so the summers are short and fresh and winters long and cold. History of the city is not fortunate because it has twice been destroyed almost to the ground - in the Balkan wars and World War II. The oldest building is the church of the Holy Transfiguration of the 1862nd year. Zabljak is host to several events, here are held days of mountain flowers, horse racing, and climb to the highest peak, Bobotov kuk (2523m). Tradition says that the town got its name from the frogs, which have their croak, believed to be announcing spring.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Main tourist attractions of Zabljak are definitely untouched nature, beautiful glacier lakes and ski sports. We should not forget rafting on Tara. The canyon of the river depth is 1300m and it is the second in the world, immediately after the canyons of the Colorado River, and is protected by UNESCO.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">In the vicinity of Zabljak has 18 glacial lakes, the most important are Black, Zminje and Devils Lake. The largest of them, Black Lake, located at 3 km from the town of Zabljak. It is actually composed of large and small lakes, connected by a channel which dries up in summer so that the lake is divided. It is interesting that the small lake has a higher volume (due to greater depth). Is a popular walking tour around the lake, which is 3 kilometers long. On the coast there is a restaurant offering national specialties, and there is the possibility of renting boats.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Most tourists on Zabljak is due to skiing and other winter activities. They have a choice between several paths for recreational skiing, but also for the more advanced alpine and nordic disciplines. Trails have ski lifts and cable cars. Although skiing is still a major sport, snowboarding is more popular in Zabljak. Interesting place is the Debeli namet where it is 200-300 meters throughout the snow-covered.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Summer or winter, Zabljak is always gladly visited destination. Peace, quiet, beautiful nature in connection with the great possibilities of planning an active holiday make it one of the most interesting destinations. Here you can enjoy the beautiful winter landscapes, go on long walks through the woods to ski, swim, and after all that sit in a cafe with a local company to boiled wine or tea with rum.</span></span></p>', '43.154541', '19.123150', 'zabljak'),
(174, 'Monastery Ostrog (En)', 315, 0, NULL, 2, 'Monastery ', 'Monastery Ostrog', 'Monastery Ostrog', 'Monastery Ostrog', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">In the vicinity of Niksic, in Bjelopavlickoj plain, is the monastery Ostrog. This fascinating example of the architecture lies along the nearly vertical edge Ostro&scaron;ka beams. Founded in the 17th century by St. Basil of Ostrog, who was buried here. There are reports of thousands of miraculous healings that are believed to have attained the power of the Holy Vassily.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The monastery is divided into upper and lower complex. The lower complex are the monastery and church of the Holy Trinity, built in the 1820th year. The upper monastery gives the impression as if cut out of the mountains. Both monasteries can be commended numerous frescos. Between them in 2005. built the church of the Holy Martyrs Stojan, and there are a number of cave churches, which represent a great historical value. Ostrog is one of the most visited pilgrimage site in the Balkans. It is visited by Orthodox and Catholics, and Muslims from around the world.</span></span></p>', '42.674931', '19.030310', 'monastery-ostrog-en'),
(175, 'Zabljak Crnojevi&#263;a', 346, 0, NULL, 2, '', 'Zabljak Crnojevi&#263;a', 'Zabljak Crnojevi&#263;a', 'Zabljak Crnojevi&#263;a', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><img style="vertical-align: top; margin: 2px; border: 2px solid black;" title="Žabljak Crnojevi&#263;a" src="../upload-media/noncomm/Zabljak_Crnojevica.jpg" alt="Žabljak Crnojevi&#263;a" width="614" height="457" />Evidence of the turbulent history of Montenegro can be found at every turn. One is certainly the most interesting is certainly Zabljak Crnojevica. This fortress is situated near the mouth of Moraca in Skadar Lake. lifteded the top of the hill, to help ensure a good strategic position. If in winter the water level rose, the mountain would become a lake. The year of construction refers to the 10th century of under the dynasty Vojislavljevi&#263;a. However, it was first mentioned in written sources in the 15 Ages. It is certain that Zabljak Crnojevica was the capital of the then state of Zeta. It was ruled by Stefan first, followed by his son Ivan Crnojevic, from 1466th to 1478 godine.Ivan was forced to move the capital because the Turks managed to conquer the city. Their power was left to the Congress of Berlin 1878th year, although the Montenegrins in an attack that could win it. <img style="float: right; margin: 4px; border: 2px solid black;" title="Žabljak Crnojevi&#263;a1" src="../upload-media/noncomm/zabljak_crnojevica.jpg" alt="Žabljak Crnojevi&#263;a1" width="433" height="325" />The city had high walls with towers and a gatehouse. Buildings in there are still well preserved. Most significant are the castle of Ivan Crnojevica and the St. George Church, which during the Turkish occupation&nbsp; it was converted into a mosque. Architecture is full of Venetian elements from the early period, but the oriental period Turkse occupation.</span></span></p>', '42.317305', '19.157152', 'zabljak-crnojevi-263a'),
(176, 'National park Durmitor', 309, 0, NULL, 2, 'National park', 'National park, Durmitor', 'National park, Durmitor', 'National park', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">It includes the plateau interspersed with many canyons, above which rise the imposing mountain peaks. For the name of Durmitor is considered to be descended from a Celtic word that means "mountain full of water," And that is exactly one of the characteristics of this national park. It beautifies 18 glacial lakes, you called another mountain eyes. The largest and most attractive is the Black Lake, while the highest peak Bobotov hip.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Tara River Canyon, located in the north of the park is particularly impressed by its beauty. As the second largest canyon in the world, but also because of the famous river for rafting, visits it every year a large number of tourists. <br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Durmitor is also popular with nature lovers because it is rich in flora and fauna. Over 1,300 species, many of which are relict, and there are 36 endemic species, of which 6 can be seen only on Durmitor. One of the few untouched forests of black pine is right here. In many forests that adorn this national park live brown bear, wild pigs chamois and wild cats, as well as various bird species. The Tara River is particularly rich in salmon.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">In this region you can find numerous monuments of culture is from the ancient period. Most of those from the Middle Ages such as the ruins of towns and villages, bridges and burial.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>', '43.126759', '19.045320', 'national-park-durmitor'),
(177, 'Rijeka Crnojevica', 312, 0, NULL, 2, 'Rijeka Crnojevica', 'Rijeka Crnojevica, montenegro', 'Rijeka Crnojevica', 'Rijeka Crnojevica', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><img style="float: left; margin: 2px; border: 1px solid black;" title="Rijeka Crnojevi&#263;a-most" src="../upload-media/noncomm/rijeka_crnojevica_bridge1.jpg" alt="Rijeka Crnojevi&#263;a-most" width="384" height="242" />This town is situated on the extension of the Skadar Lake, halfway between Podgorica and Cetinje. Apart from the direction of these two cities, to Crnojevica river can be reached by following the path of Virpazar. There is also the possibility of arriving by boat because the trips are organized from Virpazar, Vranjina and Plavnice. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">A reason to visit Rijeka Crnojevica has more than enough. Known for its authenticity, is protected by the state because of its architectural and historical significance. Within this project, a large number of ruined houses have been renovated resulting in a growing number of tourists. The most interesting old bridge that served as inspiration for many artists. He was part of the old merchant road that passed through here. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Nature here is unspoiled because the place was rather obscure and isolated. So you can enjoy visiting the old factories, printing and cinema, but and the hike to the top up or for a leisurely walk around the river. It is clean and suitable for swimming. Another possibility for discovering the many charms of the Skadar Lake and kayak rental. Crnojevica River is known for its culinary delights. Here you can taste all the national specialties. Trout, eels and carp in several ways are well known.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Due to the proximity of Lake Skadar, here you can encounter many different types of birds.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>', '42.356070', '19.024512', 'rijeka-crnojevica'),
