(189, 'Skadar lake', 375, 0, NULL, 2, 'Skadar lake', 'Skadar lake', 'Skadar lake', 'Skadar lake', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><img style="float: left; margin: 4px; border: 2px solid black;" title="Skadarsko jezero1" src="../upload-media/noncomm/skadarsko_jezero.jpg" alt="Skadarsko jezero1" width="330" height="248" />The largest lake in Blakan has an interesting history. Before the lake at this place was a large wetland. In 1858 occurred the great storm which affected to be violently River Watershed grind off the Albanian mountains. In his rush, caused the river Bojana so much material that this has shifted its bed. Thus, the wetland became a lake.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The maximum length of the Skadar Lake is 44 kilometers and a width of 13 kilometers. Not too deep, about 8 meters. It is divided into six units: Big Mud, Little Mud, mud Vucko, flooded river valley Crnojevica, Hotski Bay and the upper basin of mud. Two-thirds of the lake belongs to Montenegro, one of Albania. In it flow into many rivers, the biggest Moraca, and go into the Adriatic Sea with Bojana.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The lake is about 6 meters above sea level. One of the many things about the island is that it cryptodepression. Its surface is above sea level, and some parts of the floor below. Such sites are called the eye or submarine, and there are about thirty. The deepest is Radusa with a depth of over 60 meters. In them the water throughout the year, nearly the same. The eye is where the bleak gather in flocks and become easy prey for fishermen.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><img style="float: left; margin: 4px; border: 1px solid black;" title="Skadarsko jezero" src="../upload-media/noncomm/skadarsko-jezero.jpg" alt="Skadarsko jezero" width="330" height="248" /></span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Besides the bleak, Skadar Lake is the only habitat for carp, the species. Smoked carp is a specialty and it is recommended to all who come to these parts. In addition to freshwater fish, which here is plentiful, the lake can be found and saltwater fish, like eels and mullets.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The vegetation on the banks and the lake itself is equally varied. Of the many species of algae, white and yellow water lilies, reeds and water over the mint kasaronje. It is a plant specific to the area of Lake Skadar, special because even though living in the lake, need rain to bring a fruit. Is edible, tastes similar chestnut.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The area of Skadar Lake is one of the biggest and most important bird habitats in Europe. A variety of ducks and geese, cormorants, herons, vultures, cormorants and many others have settled here. During the winter, this bird sanctuary located in different parts of the world. Another curiosity is the holm Omar Gorica, the only known area of gray herons on laurels.</span></span></p>', '42.171002', '19.330734', 'skadar-lake'),
